# Lab: Day 3 — Linux Networking, Firewall Hardening & Multi-Host Static IP

## Lab Metadata
- Phase: 1 – Core Systems
- Disciplines: Linux Systems, Networking, Security, DevOps Foundation
- Roles Enabled: Linux SysAdmin, DevOps Engineer, SRE
- Duration: 3–4 hours
- Dependencies: Day 1 & Day 2
- Lab Version: 1.0

## Lab Overview
Configure static IPs, secure firewall rules, hostnames, and SSH between multiple Linux hosts to prepare for hybrid and cloud-ready multi-node deployments.

## Step-by-Step Execution
1. Assign Static IPs — ensure predictable multi-node network
2. Test Connectivity — verify ping between nodes
3. Configure Firewall — secure inter-node traffic
4. Hostname & /etc/hosts — enable name resolution without DNS
5. SSH Verification — confirm secure remote access
6. Document Network Config — audit trail & reproducibility

## Automation / Configs
- MultiHost_NetworkSetup.sh
- Network_Config.md

## Failure Injection
- IP conflict simulation
- Routing / ping failures
- Firewall blocking SSH

